'''Lavina Durada-Vashne Wren''' was a female [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] who represented the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]] from [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]]<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref> to [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]].

==Biography==
When the recently rediscovered ([[232 BBY/Legends|232 BBY]]) Cularin system joined the Republic in 32 BBY, Wren was elected Senator. One of her first actions was a request for an active, galactic military presence in her system, to react against the constant [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] raids on transport ships. Wren firmly believed that the military would discourage the pirates. However, the Republic (which lacked an army at that point) sent a fleet and two divisions of the [[Thaereian military]], under infamous [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] [[Jir Tramsig]], which proved ineffective for a short-term solution. Senator Wren, the native [[Tarasin]]s and some idealists were the only ones impressed by the military presence in the system.<ref name="LFC" />

At some point following an assassination attempt in [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]], she fell in love with [[Jarid DeBell]],<ref name="AOE">{{LivingForce|An Official Engagement}}</ref> and the two went on to have a daughter [[28 BBY/Legends|three years later]], whom they named [[Night Forael Wren]].

In about [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]], during the beginning of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], Senator Wren sent her Senior assistant [[Sa'arli]] to [[Almas]], to award the local heroes with the [[Hero of Cularin|Order of Cularin]].<ref name="AMA">{{LivingForce|A Mon Alone}}</ref>

Later in the Clone Wars, she was arrested on spurious charges of collaboration with the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], which led to Cularin's occupation by [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]].

